article.headline: UNC Wilmington 65, George Mason 58
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. (AP) -- Vladimir Kuljanin scored 17 points off the bench to lead UNC Wilmington over George Mason 65-58 on Monday. Montez Downey had 13 points, including three 3-pointers, and Todd Hendley added 12 points and six rebounds for the Seahawks (5-15, 2-9 Colonial Athletic Association). George Mason (12-9, 6-5) led by as many as five points in the first half, and the game was tied 26-26 at the break. The Patriots jumped to a 37-32 lead in the second half before a 22-10 run by the Seahawks. George Mason got back within three with 2:15 to play, but UNC Wilmington increased its lead on a Kuljanin layup and a free throw by Temi Soyebo. Folarin Campbell scored 17 points for the Patriots, who shot 40.7 percent from the field and allowed the Seahawks to shoot 65.2 percent during the second half. Darryl Monroe, Will Thomas and John Vaughn scored 10 apiece with Vaughn grabbing seven rebounds for the Patriots. George Mason is 1-9 when playing at Wilmington over the past 10 seasons.
